<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0787 </DOCNO><TEXT>A brief description of one of the world's first optic fiber cable networkswhich is currently being installed in the greater Copenhagen area. Thetotal length of these cables will be over 130 kilometers. The objectis to establish facilities for the measurement of temperature and electriccurrent, for monitoring the pressure in power cables and for the totalsteering of this comparatively large district heating system. (AB).</TEXT></DOC>